From 2b51fd22a1e760d2379c7068481cea829b903ba2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Daniel Vetter <daniel.vetter@ffwll.ch>
Date: Fri, 14 Feb 2014 14:01:14 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 218/479] drm/i915: Don't set PIN_MAPPABLE for legacy
 ringbuffers

commit be1fa129f5a31e78ce0a692f0e30c2ff0fad9ebe upstream.

Tighter code since legacy gem has only mappable anyway.

Split out from Chris vma-bind rework.

Note that this is only possible due to the split-up of the mappable
pin flag into PIN_GLOBAL and PIN_MAPPABLE.

Cc: Chris Wilson <chris@chris-wilson.co.uk>
Cc: Ben Widawsky <benjamin.widawsky@intel.com>
Reviewed-by: Chris Wilson <chris@chris-wilson.co.uk>
Signed-off-by: Daniel Vetter <daniel.vetter@ffwll.ch>
Signed-off-by: Pengyu Ma <pengyu.ma@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_ringbuffer.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_ringbuffer.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_ringbuffer.c
index 032b1cf..a08a377 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_ringbuffer.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_ringbuffer.c
@@ -1941,7 +1941,7 @@ int intel_init_render_ring_buffer(struct drm_device *dev)
 			return -ENOMEM;
 		}
 
-		ret = i915_gem_obj_ggtt_pin(obj, 0, PIN_MAPPABLE);
+		ret = i915_gem_obj_ggtt_pin(obj, 0, 0);
 		if (ret != 0) {
 			drm_gem_object_unreference(&obj->base);
 			DRM_ERROR("Failed to ping batch bo\n");
